</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone further simplification of the correct answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20937","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ2.9","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By using the substitution u=sin x, find ∫sin x cos xsin2 x-sin x-2dx.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"9","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.15—Further derivatives and indefinite integration of these, partial fractions","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.16—Integration by substitution, parts and repeated parts"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}